article.headline: VA Commonwealth 92, James Madison 61
article.story: RICHMOND, Va. (AP) -- Jesse Pellot-Rosa opened the game with a four-point play and Virginia Commonwealth hit eight of its first 11 shots Wednesday night, racing to a 21-4 lead and then cruising to a 92-61 victory against James Madison. The Rams (17-7, 11-4 Colonial Athletic Association) remained tied for the league lead with Drexel, which beat Old Dominion 82-66 in a battle of co-leaders. James Madison (7-17, 3-12) trailed 52-32 by halftime after the Rams made 18 of 28 first-half shots from the field. The Dukes trailed by as many as 30 after the break. Drew Johnson led VCU with 17 points, all in the second half when he was 5-for-8 on 3-pointers. Pellot-Rosa added 16 points and Dominic Jones had 15. Dwyane Broyles led James Madison with 16 points and Daniel Freeman had 13.
